page.title: 11Wildlife
page.content: There are many woods in the {Offerton}area which provide homes for a great number of wild animals. { Squirrels}are probably the most commonly seen but there are also {Rabbits, Badgers, Shrews, Moles}and {Mice. { }There is also a wide variety of birds in the area, e.g.{Owls, Doves {Sparrows, Woodpeckers, Crows, Jays, {Kestrels, Ducks}and{Magpies. As well as animals there are a number of trees, which cover a large amount of land and provide fascinating nature walks for all the family. Smaller plants attract all kinds of insects. They are mainly{Woodlice, {Spiders, Beatles, Ladybirds,}and {Flies.
